<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Eustis</persName></hi>.<note n="1" xml:id="d350fn1">Not included in House Document No.
                                225.</note></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-02-06"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                        1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Should Waller upon his release desire to bring suit in French courts,
                                based upon personal illtreatment suffered during voyage, you are
                                authorized to arrange such security for costs as will enable him to
                                sue.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>